        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>lighter than air aircraft [300216066], aircraft by form [300220406], aircraft [300212527], air and space transportation vehicles [300222210], vehicles (transportation) [300219258], Transportation Vehicles (hierarchy name) [300042929], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to  nonporous, flexible spherical or pear-shaped bags or envelope made of a lightweight material inflated with heated air or a gas that is lighter than air and designed to rise and float in the atmosphere, usually while carrying aloft passengers or scientific instruments.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para designar una bolsa no porosa, flexible y esférica realizada de un material liviano que ha sido inflado con aire caliente o con algún gas más ligero que el aire. Diseñada para elevarse y flotar en la atmósfera, generalmente mientras transporta pasajeros o instrumentos científicos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor niet-poreuze, flexibele, ronde zakken die zijn gemaakt van een lichtgewicht materiaal die worden opgevuld met verhitte lucht of een gas dat lichter is dan lucht en ontworpen zijn om op te stijgen en in de dampkring te blijven drijven, waarbij meestal passagiers of wetenschappelijke instrumenten mee naar boven worden genomen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指由輕型材質製成之無孔隙又具彈性的球狀袋，內充熱空氣或比空氣輕的氣體，設計於大氣中升空飄浮，通常是將乘客或科學儀器載運至高空。 
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Nichtporöser, biegsamer, kugelförmiger oder birnenförmiger Sack oder Umhüllung aus einem leichten Material, aufgeblasen mit heißer Luft oder einem Gas, das leichter ist als Luft; entworfen, um aufzusteigen und in der Atmosphäre zu schweben und dabei üblicherweise Passagiere oder wissenschaftliche Instrumente mit in die Höhe zu befördern.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
